President Barack Obama has proclaimed January 2017 as National Mentoring Month in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the importance of mentors in helping young people overcome obstacles and achieve their goals. Mentors, including parents, teachers, coaches, and other individuals, play a crucial role in providing support and guidance to young people. The proclamation highlights the efforts of the My Brother's Keeper initiative, which aims to address opportunity gaps and promote mentorship nationwide. The Obama Administration has also implemented mentorship programs and initiatives to expand educational and career opportunities for students. National Mentoring Month encourages individuals and communities to celebrate the transformative impact of mentorship and engage in activities and programs that promote mentoring.